---
import Site from "../../layouts/Site.astro";
const title = "Tulaa — Terms of Use (v1.0)";
const description =
    "Tulaa Terms of Use — privacy-first, optional anonymous analytics and crash reporting, no ads.";
const effective = "2025-09-16";
---

<Site title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/legal/terms">
    <main style="max-width:840px;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;">
        <h1 style="margin:12px 0 8px;">
            <img
                src="https://images.tulaa.life/logo.webp"
                alt="Tulaa logo"
                width="48"
                height="48"
                style="vertical-align:middle;border-radius:8px;margin-right:6px;"
            />
            Tulaa — Terms of Use
        </h1>
        <p class="meta" style="color:#6b6b76;">
            Version 1.0 · Effective <time datetime={effective}>{effective}</time
            >
        </p>

        <div
            style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--ring);padding:16px 18px;border-radius:14px;"
        >
            <p>
                <strong>Short version:</strong> Tulaa supports wellbeing with yoga,
                meditation, journaling, water tracking, reminders, and tips. It’s
                not medical advice. Your logs stay on your device. Analytics and
                crash reports are optional, anonymous, and never include your personal
                data. No ads.
            </p>
        </div>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">1) Purpose</h2>
        <p>
            Tulaa is a wellbeing companion. It does not diagnose, treat, or
            prevent disease.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">2) Health &amp; Safety</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Not a medical service. Consult a qualified professional before
                starting new routines.
            </li>
            <li>Stop if you feel pain, dizziness, or discomfort.</li>
            <li>Not for emergencies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">3) Who Can Use</h2>
        <p>
            Designed for adults 18+. Teens 16–18 may use with parental guidance.
            Not for children under 16.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">4) Your Data</h2>
        <p>
            Yoga logs, water, moments/journals, rhythms, and period data are
            stored only on your device. You can export or delete them any time
            in the app. If you uninstall or reset your device, your local data
            may be lost.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">5) Analytics &amp; Crash Reporting</h2>
        <p>
            By default, nothing is collected. If you opt in, we may use
            <a
                href="https://posthog.com/privacy"
                rel="nofollow noopener"
                target="_blank">PostHog</a
            >
            to collect anonymous usage analytics (e.g., which features are used)
            and
            <a
                href="https://sentry.io/privacy"
                rel="nofollow noopener"
                target="_blank">Sentry</a
            >
            to collect anonymous crash reports (technical details like device model,
            OS version, stack traces). These never include your journals, health
            logs, or personal identifiers. You can switch analytics and crash reporting
            off anytime in settings.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">6) Permissions</h2>
        <p>
            Notifications are used only if you set up Rhythms (reminders). No
            access to contacts, camera, or location.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">7) Content &amp; Ownership</h2>
        <p>
            All yoga, audio, text, visuals, and designs belong to Tulaa. Your
            personal entries belong to you. Do not copy or redistribute Tulaa
            content without permission.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">8) Free &amp; Paid Features</h2>
        <p>
            Core app is free. In future, premium plans or memberships may be
            offered; pricing will be shown clearly before purchase.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">9) Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>
            Do not misuse, interfere with, reverse engineer, or use Tulaa for
            unlawful purposes.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">10) Availability &amp; Changes</h2>
        <p>
            Features may change or be removed. Tulaa is offline-first but
            uninterrupted availability isn’t guaranteed.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">11) Warranty &amp; Liability</h2>
        <p>
            Tulaa is provided “as is”. To the maximum extent allowed by law,
            we’re not liable for indirect or consequential losses. Where
            liability cannot be excluded, it is limited to INR ₹1,000.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">12) Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of India, State of Karnataka.
            Courts in Bengaluru have exclusive jurisdiction.
        </p>

        <h2 style="margin-top:24px;">13) Updates</h2>
        <p>
            If these Terms change, we’ll show a notice in the app and ask you to
            accept the new version.
        </p>

        <p class="meta" style="color:#6b6b76;">
            Need help? <a href="mailto:support@tulaa.life">support@tulaa.life</a
            > ·
            <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        </p>

        <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
            {
                "@context": "https://schema.org",
                "@type": "WebPage",
                "name": "Tulaa — Terms of Use",
                "url": "https://tulaalife.com/legal/terms",
                "inLanguage": "en",
                "datePublished": "2025-09-16",
                "isPartOf": {
                    "@type": "WebSite",
                    "name": "Tulaa",
                    "url": "https://tulaalife.com"
                }
            }
        </script>
    </main>
</Site>
